Re: Not sure if I got this right...
by ThePacster » Thu 03.25.2010 6:22 pm Hyperworm wrote:Well, except that 「ことにしたの？」 isn't a passive construction like "Has... been decided?", but an active construction with a subject, as ThePacster translated it in the first reply to this topic.(AFAIK)Very picky but yes. 「ことにする」 is something that has been actively decided by the person, and I believe 「ことになる」 is something that is passively (is that the right word?) decided.
